<item>
            <title>[LU-11733] sanity-lfsck: &apos;Timeout occurred after 250 mins, last suite running was sanity-lfsck</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11733</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for ablagodarenko &amp;lt;c17828@cray.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/adaceaf6-f804-11e8-b67f-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/adaceaf6-f804-11e8-b67f-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test log:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
== sanity-lfsck test 31e: Re-generate the lost slave LMV EA &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; striped directory (1) ================ 17:22:38 (1543944158)
#####
For some reason, the slave MDT-object of the striped directory
may lost its slave LMV EA. The LFSCK should re-generate the
slave LMV EA.
#####
Inject failure stub on MDT0 to simulate the &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; that the
slave MDT-object (that resides on the same MDT as the master
MDT-object resides on) lost the LMV EA.
CMD: trevis-68vm7 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param fail_loc=0x162a fail_val=0
fail_loc=0x162a
fail_val=0
CMD: trevis-68vm7 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param fail_loc=0x0 fail_val=0
fail_loc=0x0
fail_val=0
Trigger namespace LFSCK to re-generate slave LMV EA
CMD: trevis-68vm7 /usr/sbin/lctl lfsck_start -M lustre-MDT0000 -t namespace -r -A
Started LFSCK on the device lustre-MDT0000: scrub namespace
CMD: trevis-68vm7 /usr/sbin/lctl lfsck_query -t namespace -M lustre-MDT0000 -w |
		      awk &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;/^namespace_mdts_completed/ { print \$2 }&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
